Gus Poyet believes his players are now convinced by his methods after their Tyne-Wear derby victory.

The Uruguayan had spoken just a week earlier about being ‘bored’ and ‘frustrated’ with his team after a run of five draws in six matches.

But Poyet feels the players have bought into his vision and says the 1-0 win at St James’ Park can prove a turning point in his tenure.

