‘This season we’ve been asking him to do too many things in defence – he has been too far from the opposition goal.

‘The responsibility is 50-50 – some of it mine because of the way we play, the other half is with the player and when he gets the chance he needs to produce.

‘You don’t score away from home in a derby three years in a row if you’re bad, no, he’s a special player.

‘This will help him a lot. I would say he will be very good over the next few games now.’

 

